<item>
            <title>[LU-5013] LL_IOC_{GET,SET}_LEASE ioctls return FMODE_{READ,WRITE}</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5013</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The handler for &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;LL_IOC_{GET,SET}_LEASE&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; may return &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;FMODE_{READ,WRITE}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; according to the type of lease. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;FMODE_{READ,WRITE}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; are internal to the Linux kernel and should not be used in this way. The only user of these ioctls is multiop so it&apos;s a good time to fix them.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
